        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You have always been near the business of selling people, graduating from being a lookout for the constables, to a recruiter to eventually a runner of your own stable of women. One day a westerner came to your brothel and said he wanted to buy in, you had no intention at first but after the third meeting, you were willing. Over the years you began to learn the nature of vampires and what they were looking for, and your ghoul extended lifetimes gave you the time to learn how to tailor your wares to their wants. Thousands of vampires visited your brothel, more then you can remember, but you listened, and in doing so you learned of the war between the Kuei-jin and your Ventrue masters. The 1000 devils tried to push in to your business as well, after rebuking their attempt you were given the embrace as a reward. You did your Ventrue training in secret, because your sire wanted an ace up his sleeve. That was all until 1999. The Kuei-Jin did a full on assault on the island, and you were able to escape with your floating haven. You sailed around Australia and new Zealand. You made friends everywhere, one of these friends said he had a gift for you but it had to be picked up in Los Angeles. You thanked him but waited out your time, (going to an anarch or a kuei-jin city did not seem like the best of ideas) but recently you have heard that the camarilla has made a place safe and are looking for people with talents. So you pulled up anchor, and pulled in to Marina Del Rey Harbor. Shortly after landing you picked up the package that had been waiting for you.. It’s a staked Kuei-jin. You have spent many nights looking at him trying to decide what to do but it eludes you. Maybe your clanmates or the help of another clan might give you the answers about this body of the enemy. \nEmbrace: 1878 (Hong Kong)  Sire: Charleston Tack (dead)"
        ],
